<paragraph id="7E5AE11CCB3ADF00FF6FF871FBF621F4" blockId="3.[151,1120,1945,1967]" box="[151,1120,1945,1967]" pageId="3" pageNumber="220">
Type-species: 
<taxonomicName id="B9E59A9FCB3ADF00FED0F871FCD521F4" authority="Zeller, 1839" authorityName="Zeller" authorityYear="1839" box="[296,835,1945,1967]" class="Insecta" family="Plutellidae" genus="Ypsolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dolosellus" subGenus="Megacraspedus">
<emphasis id="4C913D0ECB3ADF00FED0F871FE0C21F4" box="[296,410,1945,1967]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="220">Ypsolophus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="4C913D0ECB3ADF00FE51F871FDDF21F4" box="[425,585,1945,1967]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="220">Megacraspedus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="4C913D0ECB3ADF00FDA0F871FD2921F4" box="[600,703,1945,1967]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="220">dolosellus</emphasis>
Zeller, 
<number id="C82DF33BCB3ADF00FCF5F871FCD521F4" box="[781,835,1945,1967]" pageId="3" pageNumber="220" value="1839.0">1839</number>
</taxonomicName>
; by subsequent designation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7E5AE11CCB3ADF07FF6FF834FDE22747" blockId="3.[151,1436,2012,2037]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,151,464]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="221" pageId="3" pageNumber="220">
<taxonomicName id="B9E59A9FCB3ADF00FF6FF834FEDE21AE" box="[151,328,2012,2037]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Megacraspedus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4C913D0ECB3ADF00FF6FF834FEDE21AE" box="[151,328,2012,2037]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="220">Megacraspedus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is defined by the following putative synapomorphies: reduced sacculus in the male genitalia and strongly sclerotized subostial area and very long apophyses posteriores in the female genitalia. In addition, segment 
<number id="C82DF33BCB3DDF07FF6FFF54FF33268F" box="[151,165,188,212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" value="2.0">2</number>
of the labial palpus is usually very long and straight with a dense brush of long hair, and the forewing is often elongate with longitudinal stripes. These features separate 
<taxonomicName id="B9E59A9FCB3DDF07FCB8FF37FC6726A3" box="[832,1009,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Megacraspedus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4C913D0ECB3DDF07FCB8FF37FC6726A3" box="[832,1009,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Megacraspedus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the related 
<taxonomicName id="B9E59A9FCB3DDF07FB39FF37FA0E26A3" authority="Hubner" authorityName="Hubner" box="[1217,1432,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Aristotelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4C913D0ECB3DDF07FB39FF37FAA126A3" box="[1217,1335,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Aristotelia</emphasis>
Hübner
</taxonomicName>
, [
<number id="C82DF33BCB3DDF07FF66FEECFF4D2746" box="[158,219,260,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" value="1825.0">1825</number>
] and 
<taxonomicName id="B9E59A9FCB3DDF07FEE0FEECFDF92747" authority="Chretien, 1931" authorityName="Chretien" authorityYear="1931" box="[280,623,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Caulastrocecis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4C913D0ECB3DDF07FEE0FEECFE292746" box="[280,447,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Caulastrocecis</emphasis>
Chrétien, 
<number id="C82DF33BCB3DDF07FDCCFEECFDF92747" box="[564,623,260,284]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" value="1931.0">1931</number>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7E5AE11CCB3DDF07FF3FFEC0FE8F278B" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,464]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">
More than 
<number id="C82DF33BCB3DDF07FEB2FEC0FEF0271B" box="[330,358,296,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" value="40.0">40</number>
species of 
<taxonomicName id="B9E59A9FCB3DDF07FE17FECFFD36271B" box="[495,672,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Megacraspedus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4C913D0ECB3DDF07FE17FECFFD36271B" box="[495,672,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Megacraspedus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are known from the Palearctic region (
<bibRefCitation id="1A749CEDCB3DDF07FB8AFECFFB6C271B" author="Rebel" box="[1138,1274,295,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" refString="Rebel, H. (1901) Famil. Pyralidae-Micropterygidae. In: Staudinger, O. &amp; Rebel, H. (Eds.), Catalog der Lepidopteren des palaearctischen Faunengebietes, 2, pp. 1 - 368." type="journal article" year="1901">
Rebel 
<number id="C82DF33BCB3DDF07FB38FEC0FB6C271B" box="[1216,1274,296,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" value="1901.0">1901</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="1A749CEDCB3DDF07FAF2FECFFA0E271B" author="Gaede" box="[1290,1432,295,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" refString="Gaede, M. (1937) Gelechiidae. In: Bryk, F. (Ed.), Lepidopterorum Catalogus, 79, 1 - 630." type="journal article" year="1937">
Gaede 
<number id="C82DF33BCB3DDF07FAA5FEC0FA0E271B" box="[1373,1432,296,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" value="1937.0">1937</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="1A749CEDCB3DDF07FF6FFEA5FE20273F" author="Huemer" box="[151,438,332,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" refString="Huemer, P. &amp; Karsholt, O. (2001) Megacraspedus eburnellus sp. nov. and M. dolosellus (Zeller, 1839), a case of confusion in alpine lepidopterology (Lepidoptera: Gelechiidae). Entomologische Zeitschrift, 111, 238 - 242." type="journal article" year="2001">
Huemer &amp; Karsholt 
<number id="C82DF33BCB3DDF07FE83FEA4FE20273F" box="[379,438,332,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="1A749CEDCB3DDF07FE39FEA4FC8B273F" author="Junnilainen" box="[449,797,332,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" refString="Junnilainen, J. &amp; Nupponen, K. (2010) The gelechiid fauna of the southern Ural Mountains, part I: description of seventeen new species (Lepidoptera: Gelechiidae). Zootaxa, 2366, 1 - 34." type="journal article" year="2010">
Junnilainen &amp; Nupponen 
<number id="C82DF33BCB3DDF07FD18FEA4FC8B273F" box="[736,797,332,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); two from the Nearctic region (
<bibRefCitation id="1A749CEDCB3DDF07FB7AFEA4FAA6273F" author="Lee" box="[1154,1328,332,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" refString="Lee, S., Hodges, R. W. &amp; Brown, R. L. (2009). Checklist of Gelechiidae (Lepidoptera) in America North of Mexico. Zootaxa, 2231, 1 - 39." type="journal article" year="2009">
Lee 
<emphasis id="4C913D0ECB3DDF07FB4CFEA5FB7B273E" box="[1204,1261,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">et al.</emphasis>
<number id="C82DF33BCB3DDF07FB0BFEA4FAA6273F" box="[1267,1328,332,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); 
<number id="C82DF33BCB3DDF07FABBFEA4FAC9273F" box="[1347,1375,332,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" value="23.0">23</number>
from 
<collectingCountry id="06F2A18CCB3DDF07FF6FFE87FF6827D3" box="[151,254,367,392]" name="Australia" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">Australia</collectingCountry>
(Edwards 
<number id="C82DF33BCB3DDF07FE84FE87FE2E27D3" box="[380,440,367,392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" value="1996.0">1996</number>
); and one from 
<collectingCountry id="06F2A18CCB3DDF07FD8CFE98FC8727D3" box="[628,785,367,392]" name="New Zealand" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
. The taxonomic status of two species recorded from the Afrotropical region (
<bibRefCitation id="1A749CEDCB3DDF07FE86FE7CFDB727F7" author="Meyrick" box="[382,545,404,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" refString="Meyrick, E. (1920) Voyage de Ch. Alluaud et R. Jeannel en Afrique Orientale (1911 - 1912). Resultats Scientifiques. Insectes Lepidopteres II. Microlepidoptera, 1920, 35 - 120." type="journal article" year="1920">
Meyrick 
<number id="C82DF33BCB3DDF07FE1EFE7CFDB727F7" box="[486,545,404,428]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" value="1920.0">1920</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="1A749CEDCB3DDF07FDD5FE7CFD4927F7" author="Vari" box="[557,735,404,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" refString="Vari, L., Kroon, D. &amp; Kruger, M. (2002) Classification and checklist of the species of Lepidoptera recorded in southern Africa. Chatswood, Australia, 384 pp." type="book" year="2002">
Vári 
<emphasis id="4C913D0ECB3DDF07FD9DFE7DFD0827F6" box="[613,670,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="221">et al.</emphasis>
<number id="C82DF33BCB3DDF07FD5DFE7CFD4927F7" box="[677,735,404,428]" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) require verification. Larvae feed on 
<taxonomicName id="B9E59A9FCB3DDF07FB7BFE7DFB4927F7" box="[1155,1247,405,428]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
and probably on 
<taxonomicName id="B9E59A9FCB3DDF07FF6FFE50FE80278B" box="[151,278,440,464]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="221" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
